        <p>Annually, natural disasters impact the lives of over 350 million individuals. The growing frequency and intensity of these events strain our capacity to respond with the necessary speed and appropriateness. However, AI has the potential to change this process by forecasting disasters before they strike, transforming our approach from reactive to proactive.</p>
        
        <div class="info-box">
            <h3>AI's Role in Humanitarian Efforts</h3>
            <p>Artificial intelligence offers several advantages in humanitarian contexts:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Predictive Capabilities:</strong> Forecasting disasters before they occur</li>
                <li><strong>Data Analysis:</strong> Processing massive datasets to identify patterns and vulnerabilities</li>
                <li><strong>Resource Optimization:</strong> Ensuring aid reaches those who need it most efficiently</li>
                <li><strong>Real-time Decision Support:</strong> Providing actionable insights during crises</li>
                <li><strong>Communication Tools:</strong> Breaking down language barriers in international response efforts</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <p>This proactive approach is made possible by leveraging machine learning and high-resolution satellite imagery. By analyzing vast amounts of data, AI systems can identify patterns and predict potential disaster areas before catastrophic events occur, allowing humanitarian organizations to prepare and respond more effectively.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section" id="disaster-response">
        <h2>AI-Enhanced Disaster Response</h2>
        <p>The application of AI in disaster response is revolutionizing how organizations predict, prepare for, and react to natural disasters. Through advanced machine learning models and satellite imagery analysis, disaster relief efforts are becoming more targeted and effective.</p>
        
