        <p>By leveraging data and recognizing the unique impacts of various natural disasters on housing, AI is enhancing the predictive capabilities of organizations like SEEDS (Sustainable Environment and Ecological Development Society). In collaboration with communities affected by disasters, SEEDS focuses on nurturing long-term resilience.</p>
        
        <div class="info-box">
            <h3>SEEDS: AI-Powered Community Resilience</h3>
            <p>Together with Microsoft and Gramener, SEEDS has created an AI model that sifts through extensive data to pinpoint local risk factors. The model analyzes construction materials, building designs, local topography, and historical disaster data to identify which structures are most vulnerable to specific types of disasters. This united effort is streamlining disaster management strategies, easing the burdens on those most vulnerable.</p>
        </div>
        
        <p>The predictive capabilities of these AI systems allow for preventative measures to be taken before disasters strike. Communities can be educated about structural vulnerabilities, homes can be reinforced, and evacuation plans can be developed with a clearer understanding of which areas are most at risk. This shift from reactive to proactive disaster management has the potential to save countless lives and preserve livelihoods.</p>
    </section>

